cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.CV 

This paper deals with Natural Language Understanding (NLU) tasks and the use of Multi-Task Deep Neural Networks (MT-DNN) to improve their robustness against non-targeted adversarial attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the regularization effect produced by cross-task data, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with security and privacy concerns related to adversarial attacks, which could fall under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of attacks on the accuracy of the model, which could fall under computer vision (cs.CV) as well.
